  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      trans-coronary sinus intraseptal pacing (cerclage pacing)
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      This study is aimed at looking at the effect of &quot;Cerclage pacing&quot; for the heart failure
      patients who need cardiac resynchronization therapy (CRT). The study hypothesis is that
      parahisian pacing by 'cerclage pacing' may have a similar benefit as is seen with permanent
      Hisian pacing
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
